<subSubSection id="4C6F401A6009113A0C7644CA390FB64E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="B8FC56AF2E3E21B6931B9A4EE4523260" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="191CEA40741CCCE09F017899F9FE99CD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="A677F7EFFAE74302E4A2850A4C46A8EF" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mauritiana">
<emphasis id="DCBF3A9E95788B248724A8AC7C867D9F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea mauritiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but more slender (leaves mostly &lt;7 cm long) and inflorescence fewer flowered with longer secondary and tertiary peduncles so the inflorescence appears more lax. The two species are not always easily separated but were drscussed in detail by 
<normalizedToken id="07AA01C5ADA4AB668E3DEF480FEB33D8" originalValue="O’Donell">O'Donell</normalizedToken>
(1959b).
</paragraph>
